<br>
This really sickens me.  Really.  Note:<br>
<br>
-Guild was farming an item, and didn't want to share.<br>
-Someone came up and grabbed the item they were farming, got /rude in response.<br>
-That someone gave them the page, then showed up on the boards to complain about it.<br>
-That someone gets what they want, then after having flamed the guild publicly, goes about doing the same thing to them just to teach them a lesson.<br>
<br>
This isn't the first time I've seen this from that Someone, either.  Last time was when I was hunting with my wife in CB.  Here's how it went:<br>
<br>
-Calare and I were hunting the throne room for 45 minutes, and quite effectively.  We got overloaded on one of the pulls, shouted and ran to the zone.  Someone was in the path of our train, caught it, and got out alive, as well.<br>
<br>
(note that this happened about an hour earlier, and we ended up outfitting the folks who got caught for their trouble.  We tend to be nice to people who are nice, especially those who understand that, occasionally, trains happen.)<br>
<br>
-Someone spent the next 10 minutes complaining about it on the other side.  I finally told someone to stuff it and Calare and I both ran back inside.  (note that we didn't outfit this person, who was being a jerk)  This individual's last statement was 'welcome to permanent ignore'.  Hey, that's a valid perogative.  Heck, I can almost respect that.  almost.<br>
<br>
-We picked up another tank to help assure that things like that didn't happen again.  Of course, you can't guaruntee something like that, but it never hurts to try.<br>
<br>
-20 minutes later, the same thing happens.  Chain agro off of Lord Darus pulls the tower.  I hold for a minute or two, shout a couple of times, then when Calare and Tank are clear make my run to the zone.  Someone gets hit by the train.  Someone yells and screams about it again on the other side.  I commented on the permanent ignore bit, and was told that someone couldn't afford to whith all the training we're doing.  You've all heard the argument:  'don't hunt there if you can't handle it'.  Profferred buffs and heals are declined.  'I don't want your help, I've already taken your damage for you.'  I welcome him to permanent ignore so I don't have to listen to his whining.<br>
<br>
-10 minutes later a mutual friend (who had used up his Lay of Hands helping Someone who was training to zone, earlier) informs me that someone is running around the zone shouting about how horrible Calare and I are, and how we train other people who don't deserve it yadda yadda yadda.  I explain what happened and he laughs.  Says he won't use up his Lay of Hands on the yutz again.<br>
<br>
-30 minutes later I holler about a train, again, then hold for a good 4 minutes before dragging my 1 bub of health closer to zone.  I make it out to the courtyard and hold while Calare and our spare tank finish off the last of the mobs (she's stubborn that way, sometimes).  I die, and the other two in the party make it with just a sliver of health.<br>
<br>
-SOMEBODY chooses that moment to train a full health mob onto our spare tank, killing him and costing him his level.  Somebody then sends a tell to our spare tank to the effect of 'Ha ha, now you know how it feels' (got this second hand, so I don't have the complete text).<br>
<br>
-Our spare tank reported Somebody, and we didn't hear from him again.<br>
<br>
My point is, this is behavior that I've seen in the past, that I'm seeing now, and I expect will see in the future.  I had hoped that Somebody's attitude had undergone adjustment in the intervening time, but I can see now that it hasn't.  Somebody is just a jerk.<br>
<br>
/rant off <p>Denoi<BR>
